  Isothermal (363.15 K) bubble-pressure (P-x) data for benzene(1) + toluene(2).
  Values are synthetic, generated from a two-parameter NRTL (tau = b/T,
  alpha = 0.3, b12 = 20 K, b21 = 15 K) through Fugacio's
  gamma-phi bubble-point solver, but the file follows the NIST/IUPAC ThermoML
  schema so it exercises the real reader (nearly ideal solution).
  It is NOT a measured dataset; for real data use the NIST ThermoML Archive.
  Regenerate with: uv run python scripts/gen_thermoml_samples.py
-->
